Summary
I've created a complete 4-player Hearts card game with the following features:
Key Components:
HeartsGame Durable Object: Manages the game state and logic
Tracks all players and their hands
Handles card dealing and trick resolution
Scores points (1 for each heart, 13 for Queen of Spades)
Bot Players: Each bot automatically:
Joins the game
Plays cards with simple AI logic
Participates in tricks
Game Flow:
Players join until 4 are connected
Cards are dealt
Players play tricks
Scoring is calculated
Multiple rounds are played
API Endpoints:
/api/join - Join the game as a player or bot
/api/play-card - Play a card
/api/status - Get current game status


To Test

npm run dev

Then make requests like:

GET http://localhost:8787/api/status?gameId=game1

POST http://localhost:8787/api/join?gameId=game1